43
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:20,500
JCB's predecessor in interest was still using, was still accessing the property what appears to be over a gravel driveway, which passed over the corridor.

44
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:27,000
We immortalized that by entering an encroachment agreement with their predecessor and interest.

45
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:34,500
And what that encroachment agreement said is you can continue to use the gravel driveway.

46
00:03:34,500 --> 00:04:04,500
At some point in the future, what we'll do is we'll grant you a permanent access right to the bypass and if after the bypass if well after the town comes through or party comes through and builds the beach road if DOT prefers they can require that the access be removed be moved to the beach the signalized intersection.

47
00:04:04,500 --> 00:04:08,000
However, that would be on DOT's dime.

48
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:19,500
And that was basically to make the property owner whole who went through the process of building an access point to the bypass.

49
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:23,500
So that's why that clause was in here.

50
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:27,000
So the access point was never built.

51
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,500
The bypass was never built.

52
00:04:29,500 --> 00:05:01,000
